    "summary": "Tupelo, Mississippi is where Elvis Presley was born in a tiny two-room shotgun house his father built for $180. The King of Rock and Roll lived there until he was 13, when his family moved to Memphis.",
    "fullText": "Elvis Aaron Presley entered the world on January 8, 1935, in a 450-square-foot shotgun house in Tupelo, Mississippi. His father Vernon built the house with a $180 loan from his employer. Elvis had a twin brother, Jesse Garon, who was stillborn. The family was so poor that when Vernon was caught altering a check, he was sent to prison for three years, and young Elvis and his mother Gladys had to move in with relatives. At age 10, Elvis entered a talent contest at the Mississippi-Alabama Fair and Dairy Show, singing 'Old Shep' and placing fifth. The family moved to Memphis in 1948, and the rest, as they say, changed the entire trajectory of popular music. The birthplace is now a museum visited by tens of thousands each year.",
