    "fullText": "Conecuh Sausage Company, based in Evergreen, Alabama, produces a hickory-smoked pork sausage that has achieved cult status across the Deep South. Founded in 1947, the company operates from a modest facility in rural Conecuh County, yet its product is found in virtually every grocery store in Alabama and neighboring states. The sausage is made from a closely guarded family recipe and is smoked over hickory wood for a distinctive flavor. It is used in everything from breakfast scrambles to gumbo to grilled links at tailgates. Alabamians living outside the state frequently have Conecuh Sausage shipped to them, and debates over the best variety (original, Cajun, or cracked black pepper) can become heated. The company has resisted the temptation to grow beyond its capacity, maintaining its small-town production and regional identity. For many Alabamians, Conecuh Sausage is as important a cultural marker as college football loyalty.",
